

Decentralized AI, Digital Sovereignty, and Post-Quantum Security (PQC)

Welcome to AON!

AON is an open-source project under development that seeks to build a secure, sovereign, and quantum-resistant digital infrastructure. Our goal is to empower users with full control over their data and identities through the integration of advanced technologies such as Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC), Self-Sovereign Identity (SSI), and a decentralized architecture.
Current Status

Development is underway. We are seeking technical feedback and collaborators to co-create the first alpha version. Join us to explore the code and contribute!

Explore the GitHub Repository: https://github.com/magicalons/AON

Planned Architecture
Micro-Operating System (Read-Only)

Designed from scratch for resilience and transparency. It provides a secure environment for critical operations and process isolation.
APK Application

Facilitates identity management and secure connections on mobile devices.
Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC)

Planned algorithms (selected by NIST):

    Kyber (public-key encryption).

    Dilithium (digital signatures).

    Falcon and SPHINCS+ as alternatives for specific cases.

Self-Sovereign Digital Identity (SSI)

Based on Web3 standards and Decentralized Identifiers (DID). It allows users to control and audit access to their data.
Secure Identity and Device Management (SM-DP+)

Robust linking between identities and physical devices through eSIM profiles.
Artificial Intelligence

Engine for integrity validation and anomaly detection.
Decentralized Governance

The AON token will enable community participation and certification of terrestrial and satellite eSIM profiles.
Technical Roadmap
Phase 1 (0-6 months)

    Architecture design and PoC (Proof of Concept) of micro-OS.

    Initial implementation of PQC algorithms (Kyber and Dilithium).

    SDK environment preparation for APK development.

    Community audit and security testing.

    Expansion to decentralized financial services.

Call to the Community

This project seeks to open a dialogue with developers, cryptographers, and privacy advocates. We invite the community to:

    Review our architecture.

    Propose improvements or security audits.

    Participate in the development of the public repository.

Together we can build a more secure, private, and sovereign internet.


Repository: https://github.com/magicalons/AON


